By using Visual studio 2022,there are three types of projects in Blazor that are supported in visual studio 2022 (.NET8)
      1. Blazor WebAssembly (use for web apps with rich dynamic user interfaces (UIs))
      2. Blazor WebServer (run server-side inside an ASP.NET Core App)
      3. Blazor Web App (Both server-side rendeing and client interactivity)

Blazor Command 
1. add-migration initial

Database ConnectionString (SQL Server 2022) in Blazor Web Server Applications
"ConnectionStrings": {
  "MyBlazorDBContext": "Server=local/sqlserverexpress;Database=MyBlazorCrud;Trusted_Connection=True;MultipleActiveResultSets=true;TrustServerCertificate=true;"
}
